13/02/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Head of the Supreme Cassation Court Ivan Grigorov is proposing that a special commission be established at the chief prosecutor's office to investigate magistrates' assets and financial situations. Grigorov said on national radio Sunday (12 February) that he will submit the idea to the chief prosecutor and the High Judicial Council soon. The commission would be independent and consist of external experts, aimed at ridding the judicial system of corruption.
In other news Sunday, Bulgarian Interior Minister Rumen Petkov kicked off a four-day visit to the United States. He will visit both New York and Washington to meet with UN and US officials. (BNR, Darik - 13/02/06; Mediapool, BNR - 12/02/06)
